        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "RNA interference ( RNAi ) is a process",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "in which double - stranded RNA induces the post - transcriptional sequence - specific degradation of homologous messenger RNA . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "The present study was carried out",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "to apply the RNAi technology",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "to inhibit the replication of feline immunodeficiency virus ( FIV ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "Four small interfering RNAs ( siRNAs ) homologous to the FIV gag gene were synthesized",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "and transfected into a feline fibroblastic cell line",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "chronically infected with FIV ( CRFK / FIV ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "These synthetic siRNAs efficiently inhibited the replication of FIV . <S>",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "Next , we examined the effect of retroviral vector - mediated transfer of FIVspecific short hairpin RNA ( shRNA ) on the replication of FIV in a feline T - cell line",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "chronically infected with FIV ( FL4 ) . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "The retroviral vector - mediated transfer of FIV - specific shRNA was shown to markedly inhibit the replication of FIV in the FL4 cells . <S>",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "These results provide useful information for the development of RNAi - based gene therapy strategy",
            "relation": "FINDINGS"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 13,
            "text": "to control FIV infection . <S> <P>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        }
    ]
}